            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the spaghetti is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>halved cherry tomatoes </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ras el hanout </strong>and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
